# k3sraspbian (project memory)

Ansible project that provisions a lightweight Kubernetes (k3s) cluster on Raspberry Pis.
Fork/derivative of [k3s-io/k3s-ansible](https://github.com/k3s-io/k3s-ansible), adapted for
**64-bit Raspberry Pi OS** (not 32-bit Raspbian). Remote: `git@github.com:nethrose/k3sraspbian`.

This repo provisions the *nodes*. Workloads on the cluster are managed separately by the
`k3s-gitops` repo (Flux). See the global `homelab-k3s-pi` skill for how the two relate.

## Topology

- 1 control-plane node (group `k3sleaders`, host `leader01`) running `k3s server`.
- 3 agents (group `k3sfollowers`, hosts `follower01`..`follower03`) running `k3s agent`.
- k3s API on port `6443`. systemd units: `k3s.service` (server), `k3s-node.service` (agent).

## Layout

- `site.yml` - install playbook: roles `k3s_setup`, `prereq`, `download`, `raspberrypi` on all
  nodes, then `k3s/master` on the leader and `k3s/node` on followers.
- `reset.yml` - teardown (stop services, kill containerd shims, unmount, remove binaries/data).
- `roles/k3s_setup` - resolves `k3s_version` by querying the GitHub releases API at run time.
- `roles/raspberrypi` - Pi detection + cgroup flags in `/boot/cmdline.txt` + switch to iptables-legacy.
- `inventory/sample` - template inventory (SSH user `pi`).
- `inventory/my-cluster` - author's real inventory (mDNS `.local` hosts, per-host SSH users).

## Usage

```bash
ansible-playbook -i inventory/my-cluster/hosts.yml site.yml   # install
ansible-playbook -i inventory/my-cluster/hosts.yml reset.yml  # teardown
```

A reboot is expected after the cgroup `cmdline.txt` change on first provision.

## Known gotchas (do not re-trip on these)

- `ansible.cfg` hardcodes a macOS inventory path (`/Users/neth/Documents/GitHub/...`). On this
  Linux box it is wrong - always pass `-i <inventory/hosts.yml>` or fix the path first.
- CI is broken: the workflow lives in a malformed dir `.github:workflows` (colon, not slash) and a
  stray root `lint.yml`. GitHub Actions will not run until this is `.github/workflows/`.
- `inventory/sample/group_vars/all.yml` pins ancient `k3s_version: v1.17.5+k3s1`. `my-cluster` has
  no pin and uses the latest release - prefer pinning a known-good current version for reproducibility.
- `roles/k3s/master/tasks/main.yml` prints the cluster join token via `debug`. Treat that output as
  a secret; never paste it into docs, rules, or commits.
- `roles/k3s/node/tasks/main.yml` hardcodes `leader01.local` in `/etc/hosts` - keep leader naming
  consistent or this breaks agent join.
- `prereq` role contains upstream RHEL/SELinux tasks that are dead code on Pi OS (harmless).

## Hardware / network

- Raspberry Pi (64-bit OS), microSD boot. Nodes reachable over SSH.
- Networking is currently fixed-DHCP (not true static); goal is DHCP reservations on the ISP router.
  Capture each node's MAC/IP during discovery before relying on addresses.

## Roadmap (rebuild goal)

The microSD cards are failing. The intent is to reflash and spin the cluster back up *from this
project* instead of manual setup. Before depending on this repo for a clean rebuild, fix the
hardcoded `ansible.cfg` path, the CI dir name, and pin a current `k3s_version`.
